properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 5 at 2:17AM PST until January 6 at 9:00AM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the first Small Craft Advisory, northwest winds 15
to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 10 to 12 feet at 13
seconds. For the second Small Craft Advisory, north winds 15
to 20 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 9 to 11 feet at 13
seconds expected.

* WHERE...Waters from Point Reyes to Pigeon Point 10-60 NM.

* WHEN...For the first Small Craft Advisory, until 9 AM PST this
morning. For the second Small Craft Advisory, from 3 AM to 9 AM
PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PST THIS MORNING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 9 AM PST MONDAY
